Key Match Events: Nikola Jokic had 46 points and 10 rebounds, leading the Denver Nuggets to a 122-111 overtime victory over the San Antonio Spurs.
Victor Wembanyama finished with 20 points and 23 rebounds for San Antonio but was scoreless and without a rebound in overtime.
The Spurs won Friday's game 113-110 when Wembanyama stole the ball from Jokic with four seconds remaining and Vassell scored on a fastbreak layup.
Jokic scored nine points in the extra period to secure the win.
Michael Porter Jr. added 28 points and 10 rebounds for Denver.
Harrison Barnes scored 22 points and Devin Vassell 19 for San Antonio.
Vassell missed a contested layup but tipped in the rebound to tie the game at 108 with 14 seconds remaining in regulation.
Zach Collins and Russell Westbrook each received a technical foul in the first quarter after taunting one another.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was held at Frost Bank Center with an attendance of 19,038.
Referees for the game were Mark Lindsay, Brandon Adair, and Danielle Scott.
